WEBVTT

00:01.633 --> 00:04.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now:
Electric cars, are they
the ride of the future?

00:04.900 --> 00:09.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their potential to revolutionize
the road is once again
grabbing headlines, as some

00:09.266 --> 00:12.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
companies ramp up
production plans.

00:12.100 --> 00:16.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
William Brangham breaks down
the realities of the technology
and the market for electric

00:16.433 --> 00:18.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
vehicles.

00:18.533 --> 00:22.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He recorded this earlier for our
weekly segment on the Leading
Edge of science and technology.

00:22.333 --> 00:26.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The knock on
electric cars has always been
that they're a pricey, niche

00:26.900 --> 00:30.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
product that only a
handful of people would
want or could afford.

00:30.833 --> 00:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
