miles per charge.

04:56.000 --> 05:01.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's under $40,000, which
is within range of the
average American consumer.

05:03.400 --> 05:07.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then they build --
some months, the Silverado
is really, really a
gangbuster for that company.

05:09.000 --> 05:13.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when we talk to executives,
you hear the pressure to keep
those trucks going, to pump

05:16.133 --> 05:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out those F-150 profits.

05:18.500 --> 05:23.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, studies show that,
for Ford, the F-150 is as much
as 90 percent sometimes of

05:26.700 --> 05:27.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
profitability.

05:27.700 --> 05:28.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Wow.

05:28.900 --> 05:30.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SONARI GLINTON: So, you
look at the F-150...

05:30.400 --> 05:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: That's a
hard thing to argue against.

05:31.633 --> 05:34.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SONARI GLINTON: Hard
to argue against.

05:34.133 --> 05:36.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As I
mentioned, Tesla is about
to roll out this Model
3, which, obviously,

05:36.166 --> 05:40.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the big question for them is
that they have been selling a
very small number of very pricey

05:40.500 --> 05:42.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
cars.

05:42.633 --> 05:44.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now they want to sell a
lot of these cheaper cars to
appeal to a bigger audience.

05:44.466 --> 05:45.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What's the big
challenge for Tesla?

05:45.866 --> 05:49.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SONARI GLINTON: All the bets.

05:49.100 --> 05:51.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For Tesla, it's a bet inside
of a bet inside of a bet.

05:51.833 --> 05:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're betting that more people
are going to buy electric cars.

05:55.633 --> 06:00.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're betting on the battery
technology, which Tesla has
one of the biggest factories

06:00.500 --> 06:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
